name: Brock Purdy
summary: The San Francisco 49ers have suffered a significant setback ahead of their Week 12 matchup against the Green Bay Packers, as both quarterback Brock Purdy and defensive end Nick Bosa have been ruled out due to injuries. Purdy's shoulder injury, sustained during last week's loss to the Seattle Seahawks, will sideline him for the game, making way for veteran backup Brandon Allen to take the reins. The 49ers' injury woes do not end there, as the team continues to navigate an extensive injury report, with Purdy's latest setback adding to concerns about the team's dwindling playoff hopes. The absence of both Purdy and Bosa, a key cog in the team's pass rush, has put the 49ers' season in jeopardy, raising questions about the team's ability to contend in the remaining games.
